<center><font size=7><b>Velnor's Lair</b></font></center>
<center>Number of entries found: 4</center><p>
<center>
<table width=600>
<TR><TD bgcolor="blue" background=""><font color="white"><b><i>Tips</i></b></font></td></tr>
<TR><TD>If wizard's steps you are to tread,<br>
A fireball knocks the spider dead.<br>
Velnor's visions are just a sham;<br>
Bridges made of stone, are just illusion.<br>
Ogres from little acorn's do not grow;<br>
They have to be fed.<br>
In caves&nbsp;with dead-ends do not look in awe,<br>
If it's exits you want seek the hidden door.<br>
If you should fight and run<br>
Be prepared for evil to follow.<br>
It will usually get the better of you.
 <i>(Quentin Heath in Sinclair User issue 15)</i> 

<br><hr>
Finally, to get
through the Cave of Spores in <I>Velnor's Lair</I>, put the silk handkerchief around
your face and progress as normal.
 <i>(Unknown in Your Spectrum issue 11)</i> 

<br><hr>
To cross
lava, hold the statuette and say "tiamat"
then cross bridge. Extinguish torch before
going north from the giant's lair into the
swamp. To pass the sharks, drop armour,
use trident, enter pool, east, leave pool.
 <i>(Tony Bridge, Ken Matthews in Micro Adventurer issue 14)</i> 

<br><hr>
Speaking of Velnor's Lair,
the crocodiles are a bit of a
nuisance to many people.
After knocking off all those
monsters, it would only be fair
to share some with the Crocs,
now wouldn't it? To cross the
river, USE BATH.
 <i>(Tony Bridge, Ken Matthews in Micro Adventurer issue 15)</i> 
<br>
</td></tr>
</table></center><P>
